00:53:17.680 --> 00:53:18.520
Because that went down.

00:53:18.520 --> 00:53:20.200
They wouldn't be coming with them.

00:53:20.200 --> 00:53:24.280
And it's a beautiful place, then.

00:53:24.280 --> 00:53:25.480
And they just so thankful.

00:53:25.480 --> 00:53:26.960
They still have boys.

00:53:26.960 --> 00:53:30.160
They all year round their father and mother.

00:53:30.160 --> 00:53:31.520
And they just happened.

00:53:31.520 --> 00:53:33.160
And they were able to save it.

00:53:33.160 --> 00:53:35.240
And I'm so thankful to them that they came

00:53:35.240 --> 00:53:36.200
for it.

00:53:36.200 --> 00:53:37.440
It's the right time for her.

00:53:42.040 --> 00:53:44.120
Thank you, Miss Miller again.

00:53:44.120 --> 00:53:46.040
I hope I didn't.

00:53:46.040 --> 00:53:49.160
This has been a presentation of the Library of Congress

00:53:49.160 --> 00:53:51.280
and the Smithsonian National Museum

00:53:51.280 --> 00:53:54.760
of African-American history and culture.

